<TITLE> Secretary transfers made </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Dec 23(bdnews24.com)---The government on Wednesday transferred two acting and four additional secretaries. Acting primary and mass education secretary Badrul Alam Tarafdar has been made acting chairman of Land Appeals Board. Additional secretary of the ministry Abu Alam Shahid Khan has replaced him. Khan was senior assistant secretary during BNP-led coalition government's tenure, having been deprived of promotion. Acting liberation war affairs secretary Firoz Kibria have been made officer on special duty (OSD) at establishment ministry. Additional education secretary Ujjal Bikash Dutta will take his place. Additional secretary Mojibur Rahman Hawladar, an OSD, has been made chairman of The Space Research and Remote Sensing Organization (SPARSO). Additional secretary Begum Dilruba has been made chairman of Bangladesh Jute Corporation. b
